The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Usha Martin profit jumps

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Feb. 3: Usha Martin Ltd (UML) has posted a 72 per cent jump in stand-alone net profit to Rs 28.41 crore in the third quarter ended December 31, 2006, from Rs 16.50 crore in the same period last fiscal. The speciality steel and wire rope manufacturing company aims to end this fiscal with a gross turnover of Rs 3,000 crore. Net sales in the quarter stood at Rs 351.39 crore against Rs 315.80 crore a year ago. Consolidated net sales were at Rs 480.38 crore during the quarter.

 The third quarter has experienced improvement in operating margins by 2.51 per cent due to iron ore integration. The sale of value-added products grew by about 17 per cent, speciality steel production by 18 per cent and global wire ropes production by 12 per cent. Our capacity expansion of speciality steel and wire rope products by next year would be 400,000 tonnes, which would reach 1 million tonnes in three years, said P. Bhattacharya, joint managing director of Usha Martin.

 Of the Rs 1,350-crore capital expenditure approved by the board, around Rs 200 crore has been earmarked for minerals, Rs 100 crore for value addition to products, Rs 150 crore for logistics, distribution and marketing, Rs 300 crore for power and Rs 500 crore for steel-making, including rolling facility. 




